WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.080 --> 00:00:01.634
Hey, good morning family.

00:00:01.634 --> 00:00:03.508
How are y'all doing today?

00:00:03.508 --> 00:00:04.925
Well, praise the Lord.

00:00:04.925 --> 00:00:07.165
We have another video for you.

00:00:08.609 --> 00:00:19.760
I was praying last night and seeking the Lord, and he's talking to me a lot about things that are coming, things for my future, for my kids, and for what he has for us.

00:00:19.760 --> 00:00:25.739
But a lot of you—I've noticed some of the emails say, "Oh, Brother Brandon, none of that's going to happen when we're here.

00:00:25.739 --> 00:00:27.840
We're going to be taken in the rapture before.

00:00:27.840 --> 00:00:29.946
We won't see any of that stuff.

00:00:29.946 --> 00:00:32.142
" And I have to say, you're delusional.

00:00:34.436 --> 00:00:37.600
None of the other prophets are prophesying that.

00:00:37.600 --> 00:00:40.103
None of the other ministers are ministering that.

00:00:42.068 --> 00:00:45.582
What makes you think that God's only going to tell you this stuff?

00:00:45.582 --> 00:00:50.446
I have no idea why I'm the only one the Lord tells.

00:00:50.709 --> 00:00:56.399
He said, "Brandon, because I'm going to tell you, I have a lot of people try to be my friend.

00:00:56.915 --> 00:01:01.448
" And you go, "Okay, can I talk to them?

00:01:01.448 --> 00:01:02.675
Can I hang out with them?

00:01:02.675 --> 00:01:07.006
" And the Lord says, "No, I've called you to be separate unto me.

00:01:07.006 --> 00:01:16.048
You won't have friends in this because they will influence the way I talk to you because their opinions don't line up with what I'm saying.

00:01:16.048 --> 00:01:21.808
" That's interesting because I will reach out and want to talk to people and the Lord said, "That's the last conversation.

00:01:21.808 --> 00:01:24.880
Don't continue to do that.

00:01:24.880 --> 00:01:30.240
Don't do that because their opinions don't line up with what I'm telling you, Brandon.

00:01:30.240 --> 00:01:34.560
I'm trying to lead you in a direction and warn my people what's coming.

00:01:34.560 --> 00:01:37.659
" Now, what they're hearing, that's between them and God.

00:01:37.659 --> 00:01:38.980
I'm not here to judge that.

00:01:38.980 --> 00:01:42.053
I'm here to follow what the Holy Spirit tells me to tell you.

00:01:42.053 --> 00:01:47.056
And if it witnesses with you and it bears witness in your spirit, then go by it.

00:01:47.056 --> 00:01:48.479
If it doesn't, put it on the shelf.

00:01:48.479 --> 00:01:50.417
But at least I can say I told you so.

00:01:50.746 --> 00:01:53.626
The Lord told me, he said, "There's a difference, Brandon.

00:01:53.853 --> 00:01:56.747
" He said so many people say, "Lord, all these people say you're humble.

00:01:58.022 --> 00:02:00.765
" Even big ministries say, "Oh, you're humble.

00:02:00.765 --> 00:02:03.759
" And he said, "Brandon, humility is something of the heart.

00:02:12.391 --> 00:02:14.760
Either you have it or you don't.

00:02:14.760 --> 00:02:19.302
Either you recognize that it's Christ in you or you don't.

00:02:21.417 --> 00:02:24.400
It's black and white.

00:02:24.400 --> 00:02:39.839
" And I can tell you, ladies and gentlemen, if you really knew how my education was and who I really am as a person, I am—in the natural—what I perceive is a very insecure person a lot of times about things.

00:02:39.839 --> 00:02:43.876
But the Lord told me, he said, "Brandon, I've called you to be secure in me.

00:02:43.876 --> 00:02:46.930
It doesn't matter what men say about you.

00:02:46.930 --> 00:03:02.160
" And he has me on a path to tell you all what he says, and I stand with him regardless of what everybody else says—how popular you can be or who invites you to their house or their conference or whatever.

00:03:02.160 --> 00:03:04.640
I don't care.

00:03:04.640 --> 00:03:12.959
I prefer really to stay right here in my garden praying and talking to the Father and looking at my flowers.

00:03:12.959 --> 00:03:15.440
I don't care about all that other stuff.

00:03:15.440 --> 00:03:16.760
This is just me.

00:03:16.760 --> 00:03:17.420
I'm real.

00:03:17.420 --> 00:03:19.359
All that other crap doesn't matter.

00:03:20.541 --> 00:03:22.559
People try to boost up an ego real quick.

00:03:22.559 --> 00:03:27.005
I see a lot of ego in the body of Christ in the upper leadership.

00:03:27.005 --> 00:03:31.139
A lot of people with big heads that feel they're like Saul.

00:03:31.139 --> 00:03:32.439
You know what it's like?

00:03:32.439 --> 00:03:42.240
It's like Saul whenever he lost the anointing; David had it and he thought he was still called of God and God was still speaking to him.

00:03:42.400 --> 00:03:49.298
They are as dry as a desert spiritually and they're still pretending that they've got it and they don't have it anymore.

00:03:50.124 --> 00:04:01.439
I've seen it a lot and they walk around with this big puffed-up ego and spiritual head thinking the Lord's still talking to them and they haven't had a fresh word in years.

00:04:01.439 --> 00:04:03.821
They're still running off of twenty-year revelation.

00:04:03.821 --> 00:04:08.160
But God is a now God and he speaks fresh revelation all the time.

00:04:13.668 --> 00:04:22.160
I've tried to tell you all the people that you see in the forefront now won't be there soon.

00:04:22.160 --> 00:04:29.480
And you'll see a new generation of Davids rising up beyond anybody's comprehension of what's about to take place.

00:04:29.480 --> 00:04:31.462
But it's not to glorify man.

00:04:31.462 --> 00:04:33.108
It's to glorify God.

00:04:33.108 --> 00:04:37.600
And it's about him getting the glory.

00:04:37.600 --> 00:04:41.749
Ego and resume, ego and platform is no more.

00:04:41.749 --> 00:04:43.623
It's all about Jesus.

00:04:43.623 --> 00:04:52.1000
And I'm telling you, to get the work done that he wants done, you're going to see the glory move in services that you had no idea he'd move into.

00:04:52.1000 --> 00:05:00.846
You think he'd be in some big shot's service, but you'll hear that the glory showed up in a nobody's service in the natural.

00:05:00.846 --> 00:05:02.491
Do you know what I'm saying?

00:05:02.491 --> 00:05:07.170
Just because Jesus could move through them because they didn't have a puffed-up head.

00:05:07.170 --> 00:05:08.754
Their head was deflated.

00:05:08.754 --> 00:05:11.531
It was just because they were hungry.

00:05:11.531 --> 00:05:18.400
For "blessed are those that hunger and thirst after righteousness, for they will be filled.

00:05:18.400 --> 00:05:21.102
" So that's what I had to say.

00:05:21.102 --> 00:05:26.279
And then there's a lot of you who get mad about big preachers having a lot of money.

00:05:26.279 --> 00:05:30.126
And I heard you all say certain ministers, "Oh, they're the devil.

00:05:30.126 --> 00:05:31.840
They have this, they have that.

00:05:32.799 --> 00:05:40.032
" And as a person who cleaned for big ministries most of his life, yeah, it's frustrating.

00:05:40.032 --> 00:05:51.709
You see they have multi-million dollar homes, multi-million dollar furniture, flying around in multi-million dollar planes, private airplanes, private islands, going out and doing stuff.

00:05:51.709 --> 00:05:53.208
And the Lord blessed them.

00:05:53.208 --> 00:05:57.662
And you'd see a lot of the lay people in the body of Christ, they would do without.

00:05:57.662 --> 00:06:02.067
You see a lot of them working for nothing and they're sowing.

00:06:03.227 --> 00:06:04.420
They're sowing hard.

00:06:04.420 --> 00:06:04.840
They give hard.

00:06:06.940 --> 00:06:18.532
And I believe there is a balance of things that the Lord wants to get across with people because you've been burnt and you give up on things.

00:06:18.532 --> 00:06:23.200
Well, I don't believe God wants us blessed, and then you start talking bad about the man of God.

00:06:25.020 --> 00:06:31.820
I learned this: no matter how blessed I saw them, I would look at what they gave.

00:06:31.820 --> 00:06:34.133
I would look at how they gave.

00:06:34.133 --> 00:06:39.060
I would look at their lifestyle of how they would help other people.

00:06:39.060 --> 00:06:49.840
And the Bible says that if you give, it shall be given unto you—good measure, pressed down, shaken together, and running over will men give into your bosom.

00:06:49.840 --> 00:06:58.960
But if you are not in ministry and you don't have those huge platforms whenever people aren't giving those multi-million dollar checks to you, how do you make it?

00:06:58.960 --> 00:07:02.550
Because my mom and dad, we were all grunts in the ministry.

00:07:02.550 --> 00:07:03.680
All of us were.

00:07:03.680 --> 00:07:04.959
And they struggled.

00:07:04.959 --> 00:07:07.235
I mean, I live on food stamps.

00:07:07.235 --> 00:07:10.279
And you go, "Man, we believe in God just to get through.

00:07:10.279 --> 00:07:17.830
" And we're always looking for that Holy Ghost handshake—the gifts and surprises in the mail.

00:07:17.830 --> 00:07:19.779
A lot of times they never come.

00:07:19.779 --> 00:07:22.799
You would sow and sow and believe God.

00:07:23.119 --> 00:07:32.048
But I got a hold of the scripture that he gives you power to get wealth, that he anoints your hand to do something.

00:07:32.048 --> 00:07:52.640
And I got to the point where I started realizing—I'd watch how the world had ideas and the millionaires had ideas to get wealth through jobs and businesses and things like that, but they weren't janitors, but they set up side hustles.

00:07:53.970 --> 00:07:56.503
They would do real estate, they would do stocks or whatever.

00:08:01.413 --> 00:08:06.399
So I sow my seed and I start asking God for wisdom.

00:08:06.399 --> 00:08:11.479
Asking the Father, "Show me how to become the head and not the tail.

00:08:11.479 --> 00:08:19.270
" And I'm telling you, working a Monday through Friday, 8 to 5 job, making minimum wage, you're never going to do it.

00:08:19.270 --> 00:08:23.469
You're going to have to believe God for a creative idea to get wealth.

00:08:23.469 --> 00:08:29.980
I would say in the natural it's to own your own business, to have a company, to create.

00:08:29.980 --> 00:08:33.371
Ask God for what you're good at.

00:08:33.371 --> 00:08:37.724
Do something that God has anointed you to do.

00:08:38.860 --> 00:08:42.011
I've said this before, ladies and gentlemen, but it's the truth.

00:08:42.011 --> 00:08:52.895
You never see people working at Lowe's or Home Depot 8 to 5, Monday through Friday, just believing they'll get into upper management and become wealthy.

00:08:54.599 --> 00:08:56.500
We just made a good living, but you struggled.

00:08:56.500 --> 00:09:01.093
You have your little house and your little car, and we're satisfied.

00:09:01.093 --> 00:09:01.920
We're happy.

00:09:01.920 --> 00:09:07.960
But the Lord wants you to have above and beyond all that you dare ask or think.

00:09:09.100 --> 00:09:10.240
God is a blessed God.

00:09:18.673 --> 00:09:18.948
And they said, 'Well, you're a prosperity preacher.

00:09:18.948 --> 00:09:20.046
' You're right.

00:09:20.046 --> 00:09:22.423
You're right, I am.

00:09:23.474 --> 00:09:28.160
I want to see the body of Christ not struggle because I was there.

00:09:31.863 --> 00:09:32.091
I remember.

00:09:32.091 --> 00:09:35.700
Then the Lord gave me ideas to start detailing cars.

00:09:41.164 --> 00:09:48.194
I started detailing cars because I worked for a mega-ministry, and they taught me how to detail cars.

00:09:48.194 --> 00:09:50.720
They taught me how to extract carpets.

00:09:53.342 --> 00:09:53.698
I cleaned airplanes.

00:09:53.698 --> 00:09:59.084
I did things for them; I learned how to do things, wax stuff, clean, and get stains out.

00:10:05.760 --> 00:10:06.114
I learned all that.

00:10:06.114 --> 00:10:11.004
So, I took the knowledge that I had from doing that, and I created a business.

00:10:13.600 --> 00:10:17.130
I started detailing cars on the side, and I'd clean five extra cars.

00:10:19.497 --> 00:10:19.806
I'd work my tail end off.

00:10:19.806 --> 00:10:29.260
On the weekends, I only took off on Sundays to go to church because I had to work that afternoon at the church to shut it down, and I'd go out and do all day Saturday.

00:10:29.260 --> 00:10:34.160
So, I worked sometimes seven days a week until I built up enough money and we put it back.

00:10:34.160 --> 00:10:35.716
We struggled, but it took time.

00:10:41.300 --> 00:10:41.600
I would sow, and I believed God.

00:10:42.971 --> 00:10:47.209
I would detail those cars and find people in the church and hand out flyers, whatever it took, saying, 'Hey, listen.

00:10:47.209 --> 00:10:48.436
I've got a detail business.

00:10:48.436 --> 00:10:51.040
' And they would say, 'Oh, yeah, Brandon, whatever.

00:10:51.040 --> 00:10:52.999
' I'd charge a hundred bucks.

00:10:52.999 --> 00:10:53.849
A hundred bucks!

00:10:53.849 --> 00:10:56.239
Man, I was so excited to get that hundred bucks.

00:10:57.379 --> 00:11:00.418
I took that $100 and I would sow my 10% and take a little extra and believe God.

00:11:00.418 --> 00:11:05.337
If I could get an extra four cars on a Saturday, I'd work all day long for $400.

00:11:25.920 --> 00:11:26.220
I thought that was amazing because I worked hard for it.

00:11:26.220 --> 00:11:30.251
After supplies and everything, it wasn't that much because I had to buy my supplies.

00:11:30.251 --> 00:11:34.423
It was a lot, but I just kept going, building it, and working year after year.

00:11:34.423 --> 00:11:40.679
I kept building my clientele up, and then the Lord said, 'I want you to do something else.

00:11:40.679 --> 00:11:50.970
' So, I got some dogs and started raising champion bloodline dogs for special needs kids—companion dogs for therapy.

00:11:51.870 --> 00:11:58.389
You know, when my daughter got diagnosed with autism, a therapy dog was really good for her.

00:11:58.389 --> 00:12:05.040
So, I started having ideas of how to help out therapy kids and making money doing that.

00:12:05.040 --> 00:12:11.519
What I'm trying to say is then Diana had the idea for eBay, and everybody knows we've done eBay and Poshmark, and that's what we do.

00:12:22.053 --> 00:12:22.480
So, instead of getting frustrated with people and seeing their blessing, look at the seed they sowed and then believe God for your idea.

00:12:22.480 --> 00:12:23.760
Believe God.

00:12:23.760 --> 00:12:26.600
When you sow your seed, you start sowing into good ground.

00:12:26.790 --> 00:12:33.920
And that's whenever I started realizing that not all ground was created equal in the eyes of the Lord.

00:12:44.906 --> 00:12:45.253
People got mad at me when I started saying this kind of stuff.

00:12:45.253 --> 00:12:50.620
They get irritated because pastors don't like you to say that kind of stuff.

00:12:50.620 --> 00:12:56.133
They get frustrated because they don't want you to try to hamper their churches or whatever.

00:12:56.133 --> 00:13:03.371
I'm not trying to cause any ripples or waves; I just state what I feel and what the Lord shows me.

00:13:03.371 --> 00:13:09.429
So, over the course of time, the Lord has anointed me to do more and more.

00:13:11.013 --> 00:13:12.480
I want you to understand: God wants you blessed.

00:13:12.480 --> 00:13:14.651
God wants you prosperous.

00:13:14.651 --> 00:13:17.440
God wants you to have more than enough.

00:13:17.440 --> 00:13:22.750
I bring all this up because I know there's a lot of you that struggle.

00:13:39.760 --> 00:13:59.382
I try not to touch on finances very much because people get really annoyed when you talk about finances, especially in the body of Christ, because it seems that you all feel that it's been abused and I get a lot of hate from it.

00:13:59.382 --> 00:14:11.508
So I try to help you if you will listen, because I've been around the biggest of the biggest in the natural and I've watched it.

00:14:11.508 --> 00:14:15.349
I've watched how they sow.

00:14:15.349 --> 00:14:21.760
I've learned from some of the biggest names in ministry there are.

00:14:26.338 --> 00:14:28.427
The Lord has allowed me to see it.

00:14:42.160 --> 00:14:42.693
I've seen what they have, what they wear, and their closets.

00:14:42.693 --> 00:14:47.280
I've seen what the Lord's done with their lives.

00:14:47.280 --> 00:14:51.760
People criticize it, but I've seen what they give and how they sow.

00:14:51.760 --> 00:14:53.760
People go, 'Well, you know,' whatever, man.

00:14:53.760 --> 00:15:00.903
I'm going to be honest with you: I could care less what they have if their ground is good.

00:15:05.671 --> 00:15:09.360
If their ground is good and it produces and you sow into it—say they had a billion dollars and their ground is good.

00:15:14.684 --> 00:15:14.933
You don't know what it takes to make ground good.

00:15:14.933 --> 00:15:21.280
What makes 100-fold ground, and what sacrifice does it take to have 100-fold ground soil?

00:15:21.280 --> 00:15:26.260
Instead of criticizing them because they are blessed, look at their soil.

00:15:26.260 --> 00:15:28.674
Do they have good soil?

00:15:35.320 --> 00:15:35.600
Is their soil producing a 100-fold?

00:15:35.600 --> 00:15:36.159
Yes.

00:15:36.159 --> 00:15:39.029
Then there are not very many that do.

00:15:39.029 --> 00:15:41.295
So don't criticize it.

00:15:41.295 --> 00:15:48.959
Just sow into it and reap the fruit off of it.

00:15:48.959 --> 00:15:56.320
Don't be dumb, because what you talk against, you're not going to receive from.

00:15:56.320 --> 00:16:01.063
You've got to not talk against them because if you do, you don't receive the harvest off of it.

00:16:01.063 --> 00:16:02.445
I've learned: don't criticize.

00:16:02.708 --> 00:16:08.811
You get annoyed sometimes and your flesh goes, 'Man, I wish that was mine,' because that's covetousness.

00:16:15.657 --> 00:16:15.965
But I just go, 'Hey, whatever you have for me, Father, bless me in my house.

00:16:15.965 --> 00:16:21.657
' Father, you're no respecter of persons, and what you did for them, you'll do for me.

00:16:21.657 --> 00:16:29.039
So I know, God, if I sow into good ground, you said that you reap back a 100-fold return—some 30, some 60, and 100-fold.

00:16:43.600 --> 00:16:44.000
So that's what I'm trying to tell you all: ask God for a creative idea and look at the grounds that are blessed.

00:16:44.000 --> 00:16:46.770
Find the blessed 100-fold ground and sow into it.

00:16:50.845 --> 00:16:51.154
And I'm telling you, God will bless your hands, too.

00:16:51.154 --> 00:16:57.160
But some people keep giving in the same place, same time, same everything, and they don't ever see.

00:17:08.510 --> 00:17:08.780
I look at this: if you go and visit a church and everybody in the congregation is broke, check yourself.

00:17:08.780 --> 00:17:11.640
There's a problem if everybody's broke.

00:17:11.640 --> 00:17:18.250
Now, you go into some mega-churches and there's a lot of seeker-friendly and their soil is not good or whatever.

00:17:18.250 --> 00:17:24.160
I'm not saying that just because you have a rich congregation means there's anointing there or the hand's favor is there.

00:17:24.160 --> 00:17:34.896
Sometimes I go into some seeker-friendly churches and you go, 'Well, it's just because you've got a lot of doctors and lawyers here that are just looking for something.

00:17:34.896 --> 00:17:41.333
' But I'm talking about, in general, you can feel when the spirit of God is on something.

00:17:41.333 --> 00:17:43.022
Am I making sense?

00:17:44.640 --> 00:17:49.380
I hope I am because I'm trying to teach y'all something here—what Diana and I watch for.

00:17:49.380 --> 00:17:50.480
Are the people blessed?

00:17:50.480 --> 00:17:57.704
Are they spiritually set free?

00:17:57.704 --> 00:18:09.232
Are they being fed the meat of the word so that they can stand on the word of God when the storms of life come?

00:18:09.232 --> 00:18:17.520
Or are they all busted, their marriage is defeated, they're divorced, they've got sickness, and their kids are run wayward and strung out on drugs, sleeping around, and doing bad things?

00:18:17.520 --> 00:18:21.030
Is the congregation successful spiritually just as much as they are in the natural?

00:18:21.030 --> 00:18:22.649
That's what I'm trying to say.

00:18:26.711 --> 00:18:26.916
I hope that makes sense.

00:18:29.000 --> 00:18:39.210
I get a lot of flack from the emails, and Diana tells me, 'I want you to address some things and tell them where we are with that.

00:18:39.210 --> 00:18:48.360
' And so in these videos, coming up with content and telling you all things, some may be a hit and a miss.

00:18:48.360 --> 00:18:50.853
I'm listening and just pressing into Him.

00:18:50.853 --> 00:18:53.760
It's a lot of responsibility.

00:18:53.760 --> 00:18:55.679
I pray y'all have mercy on me.

00:18:55.679 --> 00:18:56.711
I'm doing it.

00:18:56.711 --> 00:18:59.679
Lord, I just thank You for every single person that's representing.

00:18:59.679 --> 00:19:04.240
He said, "I want you to take communion with My people.

00:19:16.940 --> 00:19:17.330
" I just had Chipotle chips and, Lord, we're going to take communion with Chipotle chips today.

00:19:17.330 --> 00:19:19.760
To God be the glory.

00:19:19.760 --> 00:19:21.680
It's not religious.

00:19:21.680 --> 00:19:22.920
It's personal.

00:19:33.120 --> 00:19:33.400
And Jesus wants you to be personal with Him.

00:19:33.400 --> 00:19:34.799
Don't get all flaky.

00:19:34.799 --> 00:19:38.096
People get all hyperspiritual and you got to have the wafer.

00:19:38.096 --> 00:19:39.929
And that's what I've said before.

00:19:39.929 --> 00:19:41.560
He just looks at the heart.

00:19:41.560 --> 00:19:49.119
He looks at the inward man and He just says, "Man, My kid, he loves Me and he wants to have fellowship with Me today.

00:19:49.119 --> 00:19:52.789
" We don't have to go "thee" and "thou.

00:19:54.891 --> 00:19:55.714
" I just go, "Jesus, I'm here.

00:19:57.360 --> 00:19:58.560
I just want to have fellowship with You today.

00:19:58.560 --> 00:20:00.331
Let's sit down and talk.

00:20:00.331 --> 00:20:03.120
" Do you understand?

00:20:03.120 --> 00:20:06.267
He's wanting to be your Father and a friend.

00:20:06.267 --> 00:20:09.840
He's not some God up there saying, "Where have you been?

00:20:09.840 --> 00:20:16.600
" Hey, He's there with His daddy arms and saying, "Hey, come on in, kids.

00:20:16.600 --> 00:20:20.912
Let's go have some coffee.

